title: Prairie Dogs & Burrowing Owls
name: Prairie Dogs & Burrowing Owls
description: General locations of prairie dog and burrowing owl science projects on American Prairie Reserve

properties.About: Ongoing efforts to maintain and expand prairie dog colonies are complimentary to the success of many prairie species that rely on the towns, such as ferrets and burrowing owls.
properties.Data: Data for prairie dogs and burrowing owl locations are identical due to the fact that the owls make their homes in abandoned prairie dog burrows.
